{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=12\n |EpisodeNumber2=12\n |Title=Very Few Heroes\n |DirectedBy=Bernard McEveety\n |WrittenBy=John Wilder & Jerry Ziegman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1965|4|11}}\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=13\n |EpisodeNumber2=13\n |Title=One Way Out\n |DirectedBy=Bernard McEveety \n |WrittenBy=Jameson Brewer\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1965|4|18}}\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=14\n |EpisodeNumber2=14\n |Title=That the Brave Endure\n |DirectedBy=Ron Winston\n |WrittenBy=''Teleplay by:'' Michael Dunn & John Wilder & Jerry Ziegman<br />''Story by:'' Michael Dunn\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1965|4|25}}\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=15\n |EpisodeNumber2=15\n |Title=Taste of Poison\n |DirectedBy=Ron Winston\n |WrittenBy=''Teleplay by:'' William Putnam & Nicholas Rowe<br />''Story by:'' Larry Cohen\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1965|5|2}}\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=16\n |EpisodeNumber2=16\n |Title=Price of a Name\n |DirectedBy=Leonard Horn\n |WrittenBy=''Teleplay by:'' Nicholas Rowe<br>''Story by:'' Larry Cohen\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1965|5|23}}\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=\n}}\n|}\n<small><nowiki>*</nowiki>In color</small>\n\nParts One, Two and Three of the color episode \"The Mission\" were later released as a movie titled ''Broken Sabre,'' with new footage. According to Western Clippings, the re-edited movie version ends with Jason \"regaining his commission and resuming his army career\", thus giving an ending to the series. It also ends with Jason asking a woman to marry him and she says yes. The movie was released to theaters on May 30, 1965.\n\n===Season 2 (1965\u201366)===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%; background:#fff;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#;\"| No.<br />overall\n! style=\"background:#;\"| No. in<br />season \n! style=\"background:#;\