{"title_page": "Murder of Thomas and Jackie Hawks", "text_new": "'''Thomas and Jackie Hawks''' were a couple from [[Prescott, Arizona]], United States, who were murdered in 2004. In April 2009, Skylar Julius Deleon and Jennifer Henderson were convicted of charges relating to their murders. Deleon was sentenced to death while Henderson was sentenced to two terms of life in prison without [[parole]].\n\nTwo other people, John Fitzgerald Kennedy and Alonso Machain, were also separately convicted of the killings. Kennedy was sentenced to death while Machain accepted a plea bargain after testifying for the prosecution in the trials of Deleon, Henderson, and Kennedy. He was sentenced to 20 years and 4 months in prison.\n\nDeleon and Kennedy are currently on death row at San Quentin State Prison in California. \n\n<ref name=LATimes1>{{cite news|title=Defense in yacht killings says his client did it|author=Christine Hanley|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=2008-10-08|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2008/oct/08/local/me-deleon8}}</ref><ref name=OCREG2>{{cite news|title=Final defendant in yacht-murder case pleads guilty|author=Larry Welborn|work=[[The Orange County Register]]|date=2009-06-15|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/machain-deleon-hawks-2464864-jackie-kennedy|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090620050111/http://www.ocregister.com/articles/machain-deleon-hawks-2464864-jackie-kennedy|archivedate=2009-06-20}}</ref>\n\n==Disappearance==\nThomas Hawks was a retired probation officer and bodybuilder. He and his second wife Jackie (formerly of [[Mentor-on-the-Lake, Ohio]]), owned a 55-foot yacht, the ''Well Deserved'', which they treated as their permanent home and on which they sailed for two years around the [[Pacific Ocean]] and the [[Gulf of California]]. In 2004, they decided to sell their yacht and set up home in [[Newport Beach, California|Newport Harbor]], to be closer to their  grandchild.<ref name=LATimes1 /> Jackie (''n\u00e9e'' O'Neill) had helped raise Tom's sons since their early teens, and considered the new baby her grandson.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbs.com/shows/48_hours/video/1520417861/dark-voyage|title=48 Hours Video -  - CBS.com|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=CBS|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nTheir advertisement of the sale of the yacht was answered in November by Skylar Deleon. The couple was initially cautious of Deleon, but they became more receptive when he brought his then-pregnant wife Jennifer and their other child to a meet up.<ref name=LATimes3 /> The Hawks were last seen alive on the morning of November 15, 2004, heading out of the harbor. The yacht returned, but they did not.<ref name=LATimes1 /> Their bodies have not been found.<ref name=arizona />\n\n==Perpetrators==\n{{Infobox criminal\n| image =\n| name = Skylar Julius Deleon\n| birth_name = John Julius Jacobson, Jr.\n| image_size =\n| image_caption =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1979|8|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Sun Valley, California]], US\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| alias =\n| spouse = Jennifer Henderson\n| conviction = First degree [[murder]]\n| conviction_penalty = [[Capital punishment|Death]]\n| conviction_status = [[Incarceration|Incarcerated]]\n| occupation = Former actor\n| parents =\n}}\n\n'''Skylar Julius Deleon''' (born '''John Julius Jacobson, Jr.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.orangecountyda.com/home/index.asp?page=8&recordid=387|title=Long Beach man charged with soliciting the murder of his own father and another witness while in jail on two murder cases|last=Rackauckas|first=Tony|date=2006-07-26|publisher=Orange County District Attorney (press release)|accessdate=2008-10-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/20081007/skylar-deleon-039-power-ranger-039-yacht-killing-case-underway.htm |title=Skylar Deleon 'Power Ranger' Yacht Killing Case Underway |date=2008-10-08 |publisher=au.ibtimes.com (International Business Times) |accessdate=2008-10-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024083414/http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/20081007/skylar-deleon-039-power-ranger-039-yacht-killing-case-underway.htm |archivedate=2008-10-24 }}</ref>) is an American former [[child actor]]. Deleon began acting in small parts in commercials as a child. At age 14, he appeared in the series ''[[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers]]'' as an uncredited extra in the episode \"Second Chance\". As an adult, Deleon struggled to remember lines, and his career faltered as a result. At age 20, he joined the [[United States Marine Corps]], but <!-- Do NOT change wording, THREE references explicitly support this wording -->he went on [[Desertion|Unauthorized Absence (UA)]] fifteen days later.<ref name=\"LATimes5\">{{cite news|title=What Happened to Tom and Jackie Hawks?; A couple sold their yacht in November and drove off, says the supposed buyer \u2014 and murder suspect. They haven't been seen since.|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|author=Jeff Gottlieb|date=2005-05-23|pages=B.1}}</ref> He was later given an [[Military discharge#Other Than Honorable (OTH)|other than honorable discharge]]<!-- This is different from a dishonorable discharge -->.<ref name=LATimes5 /><ref name=LATimes4>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-deleonold1,0,6683554.story |title='He did it. I know he did it,' man says of son |last=Hanley |first=Christine |date=2007-05-28 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |accessdate=2008-10-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081010005928/http://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-deleonold1,0,6683554.story |archivedate=October 10, 2008 }}</ref>\n\n=== Others involved ===\n* Jennifer Henderson, wife of Deleon.\n* Alonso Machain, former Seal Beach correctional officer who met Deleon while Deleon was serving time in prison for burglary. \n* John Fitzgerald Kennedy, Insane Crips gang member in Long Beach and former youth pastor, ex-convict for attempted murder, recruited the same day of the murder.\n* Myron Sandora Gardner, Sr., former Insane Crips gang member and ex-convict for involuntary manslaughter, who met Deleon at work after Deleon's release from prison, declined to participate in the crime but introduced Deleon to Kennedy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/deleon-112735-jarvi-couple.html|title=Judge orders lethal injection in yacht-murder case|work=[[Orange County Register]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.dailypilot.com/2005-04-23/news/export2428_1_speedy-trial-plot-jackie-hawks|title=Plot to kill a witness alleged|work=[[Daily Pilot]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/gardner-69099-deleon-beach.html|title=Defendant: Myron Gardner|work=[[Orange County Register]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Investigation ==\nPolice inquired into the couple's disappearance. On November 26, 2004, an attempt was made to access the Hawkses' bank account from [[Mexico]]. The family was notified and filed a missing-persons report with the [[Carlsbad, California|Carlsbad]] police department.<ref name=LATimes1 />\n\nOn November 29, the police interviewed Skylar Deleon. He told them that he bought the boat from the Hawkses and showed them proof-of-purchase documents. He stated to police that the Hawkses left in their car with his money, denied being in their car, and named Alonso Machain as witness to the purchase. The reason that he bought the boat, he claimed, was that he intended to launder money related to an armed burglary in 2002 for which he had been convicted.<ref name=LATimes2>{{cite news|title=3 Face Murder Charges in Disappearance of Boat Owners|date=2005-03-05|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|pages=B.1|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2005/mar/05/local/me-yacht5|author1=Stuart Pfeifer|author2=Jeff Gottlieb |lastauthoramp=yes }}</ref><ref name=arizona />\n\nIn March 2005, after initially fleeing to Mexico and then returning, Machain confessed to the crime. He was arrested in connection with the couple's disappearance along with Deleon and Deleon's wife Jennifer. Skylar Deleon initially maintained his innocence, claiming that he was not present at the time and speculating that the Hawkses were killed over a drug deal gone bad.<ref name=arizona /><ref>{{cite news|title=Police arrest two more in deaths of Arizona couple off Newport Beach|author=Ben Fox|publisher=[[Associated Press]]|date=2005-03-04|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/kennedy-hawks-deleon-2321043-jury-machain|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090511043235/http://www.ocregister.com/articles/kennedy-hawks-deleon-2321043-jury-machain|archivedate=2009-05-11}}</ref>\n\n== Trials ==\nAuthorities alleged that during a [[sea trial]] of the boat in [[Newport Beach, California#Harbor|Newport Beach Harbor]] a few days after meeting the Hawks, Deleon and his accomplices \u2014 Alonso Machain and John Fitzgerald Kennedy \u2014 bound and gagged the couple and threw them overboard, tied to the yacht's anchor.<ref name=LATimes3>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-deleon8-2008oct08,0,6703001.story|title=Skylar Deleon goes on trial in killing of yacht owners|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=2008-10-08 | first=Christine | last=Hanley | accessdate=2010-05-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/10/07/yacht.killings.trial.ap/index.html?iref=mpstoryview |title='Power Ranger' faces death penalty in yacht killings. |work=[[CNN.com]] |date=2007-10-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081108112005/http://www.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/10/07/yacht.killings.trial.ap/index.html?iref=mpstoryview |archivedate=November 8, 2008 }}</ref> Deleon allegedly masterminded the plan to kill the couple for financial gain and enlisted Machain to help.<ref name=arizona>{{cite news|url=http://www.azcentral.com/specials/special27/articles/0415hawks0415.html|title=Prescott couple took fatal voyage|last=Wagner|first=Dennis|date=2007-04-15|work=The Arizona Republic|accessdate=2008-09-24}}</ref><ref name=timespubs1>{{cite web|url=http://www.timespublications.com/jan07-feature1.asp|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130204181515/http://www.timespublications.com/jan07-feature1.asp|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-02-04|title=Depths of Evil|date=November 2006|publisher=timespublications.com|accessdate=2008-09-25}}</ref><ref name=\"dailypilot\">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailypilot.com/articles/2006/08/08/publicsafety/dpt-deleon01.txt|title=Deleon pleads not guilty to murder plot|last=Vane|first=Lauren|date=2006-08-04|work=dailypilot.com|accessdate=2008-09-25}}</ref>\n\nDeleon's wife, Jennifer, was found guilty on two counts of [[Murder#Degrees of murder in the United States|first degree murder]] on November 17, 2006, after four hours of jury deliberation. In October 2007, Jennifer Deleon (now calling herself Jennifer Henderson, since her divorce from Skylar Deleon) was sentenced to two life terms without the possibility of parole.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,299837,00.html|title=California Mother Convicted in Plot to Kill Couple for Yacht Sentenced to Life Terms|date=2007-10-06|publisher=[[Fox News]]|accessdate=2008-09-24}}</ref> She is currently housed at [[Central California Women's Facility]] in [[Chowchilla, California]].<ref name=\"State of California Inmate Locator\">{{cite web|title=State of California Inmate Locator|url=http://inmatelocator.cdcr.ca.gov/Results.aspx|website=California Department of Corrections & Rehabilitation|publisher=CA.gov|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nWhile awaiting trial in jail, Skylar Deleon was also charged with soliciting another inmate to murder his abusive father and his cousin. He was also accused of killing John Jarvi, a resident of [[Anaheim, California|Anaheim]] who was found dead in [[Mexico]] in 2003. Deleon's father and cousin (who was charged as an accessory to the Jarvi murder) are considered \"important witnesses\" in both murder cases.<ref name=\"dailypilot\" /> On March 13, 2008, Deleon partially severed his penis with a razor blade while being held in jail.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.presstelegram.com/news/ci_9846250|title=Man awaiting trial tries to 'saw off' his penis|work=Long Beach Press Telegram|date=July 2008|accessdate=July 10, 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081010022034/http://www.presstelegram.com/news/ci_9846250|archivedate=October 10, 2008}}</ref> After receiving medical attention, he was returned to jail the following day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2008/jul/12/local/me-deleon12|title=Accused killer attempts to sever own penis in O.C. jail |last=Reyes|first=David|date=2008-07-12|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=2008-09-24}}</ref> In an interview with ABC's ''20/20'', Deleon indicated that he attempted to cut off his penis because he wanted to be a woman. Defense lawyers claimed that Deleon's need for money to finance a sex-change operation was the motivation for the Hawkses' murders.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/17534/power-ranger-skylar-deleon-claims-he-murdered-for-a-sex-change-operation|title=Power Ranger Skylar DeLeon claims he murdered for a sex change operation|work=The Inquisitr News|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/TheLaw/story?id=6813191|title=Yacht Murderer Wanted Sexual Reassignment Surgery|author= Jim Avila, Greg Fisher, Christina Caron, and Kimi Culpjim Avila via [[20/20 (U.S. TV series)|20/20]]|work=[[ABC News]]|date=6 February 2009|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| author =Anna Glezer, MD, Dale E. McNiel, and Ren\u00e9e L. Binder, MD| title =Transgendered and Incarcerated: A Review of the Literature, Current Policies and Laws, and Ethics| quote =| newspaper =[[Journal of the American Academy of Psychiatry and the Law]]| date =2013| url =http://www.jaapl.org/content/41/4/551.full.pdf| accessdate =September 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn September 22, 2008, jury selection began in the case against Skylar Deleon.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/deleon-trial-jurors-2166497-first-case|title=Jury selection under way in yacht murder case|last=Welborn|first=Larry|date=2008-09-22|work=[[Orange County Register]]|accessdate=2008-09-24|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081007163257/http://www.ocregister.com/articles/deleon-trial-jurors-2166497-first-case|archivedate=2008-10-07}}</ref> In a consolidated case, Deleon was jointly tried for the murders of Thomas and Jackie Hawks as well as the murder of John Jarvi. Despite Deleon's earlier protestations of innocence, once his trial began, Deleon's attorney conceded that Deleon had indeed committed all three murders. The attorney said that he had taken the case to trial only to argue to a jury that Deleon should not be sentenced to death.<ref>{{cite news|date=2008-10-08 |url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/10/07/yacht.killings.trial.ap/index.html?iref=newssearch |title=Ex-actor guilty of yacht killings, defense says |work=[[CNN.com]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024113539/http://www.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/10/07/yacht.killings.trial.ap/index.html?iref=newssearch |archivedate=October 24, 2008 }}</ref> On October 20, Deleon was convicted of three counts of first-degree murder with special circumstances for financial gain and multiple victims and on November 6, 2008, the jury rendered a death verdict.<ref>{{cite news |first=My-Thuan |last=Tran |title=Death sentence in murder of yacht owners |url=http://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-deleon7-2008nov07,0,1127851.story |work=Los Angeles Times |publisher= |date=2008-11-06 |accessdate=2008-11-07 }}</ref> Sentencing was originally scheduled for January 16, 2009,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/11/06/yacht.killings.ap/index.html |title=Jury recommends death penalty in yacht killings |date=November 6, 2008 |publisher=[[CNN.com]] |accessdate=2008-11-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081110100734/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/11/06/yacht.killings.ap/index.html |archivedate=November 10, 2008 }}</ref> but was then rescheduled to March 20 on request by Deleon's attorney.<ref>{{cite web|first=Joseph|last=Serna|url=http://www.dailypilot.com/articles/2009/01/16/topstory/dpt-sentencing011709.txt|title=Sentencing delayed for area couple\u2019s killer|date=January 16, 2009|publisher=dailypilot.com|accessdate=2009-01-24}}</ref> On March 13, it was announced that sentencing would again be rescheduled, to April 10, so that the family of the victims could attend.<ref>{{cite web|first=Joseph|last=Serna|url=http://www.dailypilot.com/articles/2009/03/20/topstory/dpt-deleonsentencing032109.txt|title=Deleon to wait for his fate|date=March 13, 2009|publisher=dailypilot.com|accessdate=2009-03-27}}</ref> On April 10, 2009, Deleon was sentenced to death by Orange County Superior Court Judge Frank Fasel.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2009/04/skylar-deleon-gets-death-sentence-in-newport-yacht-murders.html|title=Skylar Deleon gets death sentence in Newport Beach yacht murders|date=April 10, 2009|publisher=[[latimes.com]]|accessdate=2009-04-11}}</ref> He is on [[death row]] at [[San Quentin State Prison]].\n\nOn February 19, 2009, John Fitzgerald Kennedy was found guilty on two counts of first degree murder after fewer than three hours of jury deliberation.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Welborn|first1=Larry|title=3rd man convicted in murders of couple on yacht|url=http://www.ocregister.com/news/deleon-111998-kennedy-hawks.html|website=The Orange County Register|publisher=Digital First Media|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref> He was sentenced to death on May 1, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Serna|first1=Joseph|title=Second killer given death|url=http://articles.dailypilot.com/2009-05-01/news/dpt-kennedy05022009_1_skylar-deleon-sentenced-penalty|website=Daily Pilot|publisher=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref> Like Deleon, Kennedy is on death row at [[San Quentin State Prison]].\n\nAlonso Machain, after testifying against Deleon, Henderson, and Kennedy, pleaded guilty to two counts each of voluntary manslaughter, kidnapping, and robbery. On June 15, 2009, he was sentenced to 20 years, 4 months. He likely will not be up for parole until 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/machain-113743-deleon-hawks.html?page=2|title=Final defendant in yacht-murder case pleads guilty|work=[[Orange County Register]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref> He is currently serving his sentence at [[Valley State Prison]] in [[Chowchilla, California]].<ref name=\"State of California Inmate Locator\"/>\n\nIn March 2009, after spending four years incarcerated, Myron Gardner pleaded guilty to \"accessory after the fact\" and the murder charges against him were dropped.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/man-sentenced-in-drowning-of-yacht-owners/|title=Man Sentenced In Drowning Of Yacht Owners|date=11 April 2009|work=[[CBS News]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jun/20/local/me-death-boat20|title=Murdered couple's yacht to be put up for sale|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.dailypilot.com/2009-03-26/news/dpt-gardner032709_1_ryan-hawks-myron-gardner-skylar-deleon|title=Man is freed in plea deal|work=[[Daily Pilot]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==In the media==\n* This case was investigated on TV by [[Aphrodite Jones]] in her [[Investigation Discovery]] documentary TV series ''True Crime with Aphrodite Jones'' (Season 1, episode 9), and would also be explored on the same network on two other programs: ''Wicked Attraction'' (episode \"Calm Before the Storm\") and ''Deadly Sins'' (episode \"I'd Kill For A Sex Change\").\n* This case is referred to in a segment of the \"Caffeine-Induced Aneurysm\" episode of ''[[Robot Chicken]]''.\n* This case was investigated on TV on [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] on the TV show ''[[Snapped: Killer Couples]]'', a spin-off of ''[[Snapped]]''.\n* The ''[[48 Hours (TV series)|48 Hours]]'' episode \"Dark Voyage\" covers this crime.\n* The ''[[Demons in the City of Angels]]'' episode ''Child Actor Killer'' covers the case.\n* This case is also covered in the podcast \"Killafornia Dreaming: True Crime Tales from the Golden State; Episode 14, The Tale of Lost at Sea\" - Google Play Podcasts\n* This case is briefly mentioned in the Podcast \"Raised by TV\" hosted by comedians [[Lauren Lapkus]] and [[Jon Gabrus]] in the episode \"Mt. Crushmore\".\n* This case is covered on the TV show [[Crime Watch Daily]] with Chris Hansen, Season 2, Episode 165, \"The Final Voyage\"\n* This case is mentioned in the podcast \"My Favorite Murder\" in the Episode 169, \"This Old Sandwich\"\n*This case was investigated on [[ABC 20/20]] episode \u201cOverboard\u201d\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{cite book|title=Dead Reckoning|author=[[Caitlin Rother]]|publisher=Kensington|year=2011|isbn=9780786022175}}\n* {{cite book|title=Vanished at Sea|author=Tina Dirmann|publisher=Macmillan|year=2008|isbn=9780312941970}}\n* {{cite news|date=2005-08-15 |title=Yacht murder case looks like true-crime sequel |author=Frank Mickadeit |url=http://www.ocregister.com/ocr/sections/local/local_columns/article_632770.php |work=[[Orange County Register|Orange County Register Communications]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090210113934/http://www.ocregister.com/ocr/sections/local/local_columns/article_632770.php |archivedate=February 10, 2009 }}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Capital punishment in California]]\n* [[List of solved missing persons cases]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|2117623|Skylar Deleon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hawks, Thomas and Jackie}}\n[[Category:2000s missing person cases]]\n[[Category:2004 in California]]\n[[Category:2004 murders in the United States]]\n[[Category:American murder victims]]\n[[Category:Deaths by person in the United States]]\n[[Category:History of Orange County, California]]\n[[Category:Missing person cases in California]]\n[[Category:Murder convictions without a body]]\n[[Category:Newport Beach, California]]\n[[Category:People murdered in California]]\n", "text_old": "'''Thomas and Jackie Hawks''' were a couple from [[Prescott, Arizona]], United States, who were murdered in 2004. In April 2009, Skylar Julius Deleon and Jennifer Henderson were convicted of charges relating to their murders. Deleon was sentenced to death while Henderson was sentenced to two terms of life in prison without [[parole]].\n\nTwo other people, John Fitzgerald Kennedy and Alonso Machain, were also separately convicted of the killings. Kennedy was sentenced to death while Machain accepted a plea bargain after testifying for the prosecution in the trials of Deleon, Henderson, and Kennedy. He was sentenced to 20 years and 4 months in prison.<ref name=LATimes1>{{cite news|title=Defense in yacht killings says his client did it|author=Christine Hanley|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=2008-10-08|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2008/oct/08/local/me-deleon8}}</ref><ref name=OCREG2>{{cite news|title=Final defendant in yacht-murder case pleads guilty|author=Larry Welborn|work=[[The Orange County Register]]|date=2009-06-15|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/machain-deleon-hawks-2464864-jackie-kennedy|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090620050111/http://www.ocregister.com/articles/machain-deleon-hawks-2464864-jackie-kennedy|archivedate=2009-06-20}}</ref>\n\n==Disappearance==\nThomas Hawks was a retired probation officer and bodybuilder. He and his second wife Jackie (formerly of [[Mentor-on-the-Lake, Ohio]]), owned a 55-foot yacht, the ''Well Deserved'', which they treated as their permanent home and on which they sailed for two years around the [[Pacific Ocean]] and the [[Gulf of California]]. In 2004, they decided to sell their yacht and set up home in [[Newport Beach, California|Newport Harbor]], to be closer to their  grandchild.<ref name=LATimes1 /> Jackie (''n\u00e9e'' O'Neill) had helped raise Tom's sons since their early teens, and considered the new baby her grandson.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbs.com/shows/48_hours/video/1520417861/dark-voyage|title=48 Hours Video -  - CBS.com|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=CBS|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nTheir advertisement of the sale of the yacht was answered in November by Skylar Deleon. The couple was initially cautious of Deleon, but they became more receptive when he brought his then-pregnant wife Jennifer and their other child to a meet up.<ref name=LATimes3 /> The Hawks were last seen alive on the morning of November 15, 2004, heading out of the harbor. The yacht returned, but they did not.<ref name=LATimes1 /> Their bodies have not been found.<ref name=arizona />\n\n==Perpetrators==\n{{Infobox criminal\n| image =\n| name = Skylar Julius Deleon\n| birth_name = John Julius Jacobson, Jr.\n| image_size =\n| image_caption =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1979|8|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Sun Valley, California]], US\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| alias =\n| spouse = Jennifer Henderson\n| conviction = First degree [[murder]]\n| conviction_penalty = [[Capital punishment|Death]]\n| conviction_status = [[Incarceration|Incarcerated]]\n| occupation = Former actor\n| parents =\n}}\n\n'''Skylar Julius Deleon''' (born '''John Julius Jacobson, Jr.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.orangecountyda.com/home/index.asp?page=8&recordid=387|title=Long Beach man charged with soliciting the murder of his own father and another witness while in jail on two murder cases|last=Rackauckas|first=Tony|date=2006-07-26|publisher=Orange County District Attorney (press release)|accessdate=2008-10-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/20081007/skylar-deleon-039-power-ranger-039-yacht-killing-case-underway.htm |title=Skylar Deleon 'Power Ranger' Yacht Killing Case Underway |date=2008-10-08 |publisher=au.ibtimes.com (International Business Times) |accessdate=2008-10-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024083414/http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/20081007/skylar-deleon-039-power-ranger-039-yacht-killing-case-underway.htm |archivedate=2008-10-24 }}</ref>) is an American former [[child actor]]. Deleon began acting in small parts in commercials as a child. At age 14, he appeared in the series ''[[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers]]'' as an uncredited extra in the episode \"Second Chance\". As an adult, Deleon struggled to remember lines, and his career faltered as a result. At age 20, he joined the [[United States Marine Corps]], but <!-- Do NOT change wording, THREE references explicitly support this wording -->he went on [[Desertion|Unauthorized Absence (UA)]] fifteen days later.<ref name=\"LATimes5\">{{cite news|title=What Happened to Tom and Jackie Hawks?; A couple sold their yacht in November and drove off, says the supposed buyer \u2014 and murder suspect. They haven't been seen since.|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|author=Jeff Gottlieb|date=2005-05-23|pages=B.1}}</ref> He was later given an [[Military discharge#Other Than Honorable (OTH)|other than honorable discharge]]<!-- This is different from a dishonorable discharge -->.<ref name=LATimes5 /><ref name=LATimes4>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-deleonold1,0,6683554.story |title='He did it. I know he did it,' man says of son |last=Hanley |first=Christine |date=2007-05-28 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |accessdate=2008-10-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081010005928/http://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-deleonold1,0,6683554.story |archivedate=October 10, 2008 }}</ref>\n\n=== Others involved ===\n* Jennifer Henderson, wife of Deleon.\n* Alonso Machain, former Seal Beach correctional officer who met Deleon while Deleon was serving time in prison for burglary. \n* John Fitzgerald Kennedy, Insane Crips gang member in Long Beach and former youth pastor, ex-convict for attempted murder, recruited the same day of the murder.\n* Myron Sandora Gardner, Sr., former Insane Crips gang member and ex-convict for involuntary manslaughter, who met Deleon at work after Deleon's release from prison, declined to participate in the crime but introduced Deleon to Kennedy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/deleon-112735-jarvi-couple.html|title=Judge orders lethal injection in yacht-murder case|work=[[Orange County Register]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.dailypilot.com/2005-04-23/news/export2428_1_speedy-trial-plot-jackie-hawks|title=Plot to kill a witness alleged|work=[[Daily Pilot]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/gardner-69099-deleon-beach.html|title=Defendant: Myron Gardner|work=[[Orange County Register]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Investigation ==\nPolice inquired into the couple's disappearance. On November 26, 2004, an attempt was made to access the Hawkses' bank account from [[Mexico]]. The family was notified and filed a missing-persons report with the [[Carlsbad, California|Carlsbad]] police department.<ref name=LATimes1 />\n\nOn November 29, the police interviewed Skylar Deleon. He told them that he bought the boat from the Hawkses and showed them proof-of-purchase documents. He stated to police that the Hawkses left in their car with his money, denied being in their car, and named Alonso Machain as witness to the purchase. The reason that he bought the boat, he claimed, was that he intended to launder money related to an armed burglary in 2002 for which he had been convicted.<ref name=LATimes2>{{cite news|title=3 Face Murder Charges in Disappearance of Boat Owners|date=2005-03-05|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|pages=B.1|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2005/mar/05/local/me-yacht5|author1=Stuart Pfeifer|author2=Jeff Gottlieb |lastauthoramp=yes }}</ref><ref name=arizona />\n\nIn March 2005, after initially fleeing to Mexico and then returning, Machain confessed to the crime. He was arrested in connection with the couple's disappearance along with Deleon and Deleon's wife Jennifer. Skylar Deleon initially maintained his innocence, claiming that he was not present at the time and speculating that the Hawkses were killed over a drug deal gone bad.<ref name=arizona /><ref>{{cite news|title=Police arrest two more in deaths of Arizona couple off Newport Beach|author=Ben Fox|publisher=[[Associated Press]]|date=2005-03-04|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/kennedy-hawks-deleon-2321043-jury-machain|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090511043235/http://www.ocregister.com/articles/kennedy-hawks-deleon-2321043-jury-machain|archivedate=2009-05-11}}</ref>\n\n== Trials ==\nAuthorities alleged that during a [[sea trial]] of the boat in [[Newport Beach, California#Harbor|Newport Beach Harbor]] a few days after meeting the Hawks, Deleon and his accomplices \u2014 Alonso Machain and John Fitzgerald Kennedy \u2014 bound and gagged the couple and threw them overboard, tied to the yacht's anchor.<ref name=LATimes3>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-deleon8-2008oct08,0,6703001.story|title=Skylar Deleon goes on trial in killing of yacht owners|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=2008-10-08 | first=Christine | last=Hanley | accessdate=2010-05-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/10/07/yacht.killings.trial.ap/index.html?iref=mpstoryview |title='Power Ranger' faces death penalty in yacht killings. |work=[[CNN.com]] |date=2007-10-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081108112005/http://www.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/10/07/yacht.killings.trial.ap/index.html?iref=mpstoryview |archivedate=November 8, 2008 }}</ref> Deleon allegedly masterminded the plan to kill the couple for financial gain and enlisted Machain to help.<ref name=arizona>{{cite news|url=http://www.azcentral.com/specials/special27/articles/0415hawks0415.html|title=Prescott couple took fatal voyage|last=Wagner|first=Dennis|date=2007-04-15|work=The Arizona Republic|accessdate=2008-09-24}}</ref><ref name=timespubs1>{{cite web|url=http://www.timespublications.com/jan07-feature1.asp|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130204181515/http://www.timespublications.com/jan07-feature1.asp|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-02-04|title=Depths of Evil|date=November 2006|publisher=timespublications.com|accessdate=2008-09-25}}</ref><ref name=\"dailypilot\">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailypilot.com/articles/2006/08/08/publicsafety/dpt-deleon01.txt|title=Deleon pleads not guilty to murder plot|last=Vane|first=Lauren|date=2006-08-04|work=dailypilot.com|accessdate=2008-09-25}}</ref>\n\nDeleon's wife, Jennifer, was found guilty on two counts of [[Murder#Degrees of murder in the United States|first degree murder]] on November 17, 2006, after four hours of jury deliberation. In October 2007, Jennifer Deleon (now calling herself Jennifer Henderson, since her divorce from Skylar Deleon) was sentenced to two life terms without the possibility of parole.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,299837,00.html|title=California Mother Convicted in Plot to Kill Couple for Yacht Sentenced to Life Terms|date=2007-10-06|publisher=[[Fox News]]|accessdate=2008-09-24}}</ref> She is currently housed at [[Central California Women's Facility]] in [[Chowchilla, California]].<ref name=\"State of California Inmate Locator\">{{cite web|title=State of California Inmate Locator|url=http://inmatelocator.cdcr.ca.gov/Results.aspx|website=California Department of Corrections & Rehabilitation|publisher=CA.gov|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nWhile awaiting trial in jail, Skylar Deleon was also charged with soliciting another inmate to murder his abusive father and his cousin. He was also accused of killing John Jarvi, a resident of [[Anaheim, California|Anaheim]] who was found dead in [[Mexico]] in 2003. Deleon's father and cousin (who was charged as an accessory to the Jarvi murder) are considered \"important witnesses\" in both murder cases.<ref name=\"dailypilot\" /> On March 13, 2008, Deleon partially severed his penis with a razor blade while being held in jail.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.presstelegram.com/news/ci_9846250|title=Man awaiting trial tries to 'saw off' his penis|work=Long Beach Press Telegram|date=July 2008|accessdate=July 10, 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081010022034/http://www.presstelegram.com/news/ci_9846250|archivedate=October 10, 2008}}</ref> After receiving medical attention, he was returned to jail the following day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2008/jul/12/local/me-deleon12|title=Accused killer attempts to sever own penis in O.C. jail |last=Reyes|first=David|date=2008-07-12|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=2008-09-24}}</ref> In an interview with ABC's ''20/20'', Deleon indicated that he attempted to cut off his penis because he wanted to be a woman. Defense lawyers claimed that Deleon's need for money to finance a sex-change operation was the motivation for the Hawkses' murders.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/17534/power-ranger-skylar-deleon-claims-he-murdered-for-a-sex-change-operation|title=Power Ranger Skylar DeLeon claims he murdered for a sex change operation|work=The Inquisitr News|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/TheLaw/story?id=6813191|title=Yacht Murderer Wanted Sexual Reassignment Surgery|author= Jim Avila, Greg Fisher, Christina Caron, and Kimi Culpjim Avila via [[20/20 (U.S. TV series)|20/20]]|work=[[ABC News]]|date=6 February 2009|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| author =Anna Glezer, MD, Dale E. McNiel, and Ren\u00e9e L. Binder, MD| title =Transgendered and Incarcerated: A Review of the Literature, Current Policies and Laws, and Ethics| quote =| newspaper =[[Journal of the American Academy of Psychiatry and the Law]]| date =2013| url =http://www.jaapl.org/content/41/4/551.full.pdf| accessdate =September 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn September 22, 2008, jury selection began in the case against Skylar Deleon.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/deleon-trial-jurors-2166497-first-case|title=Jury selection under way in yacht murder case|last=Welborn|first=Larry|date=2008-09-22|work=[[Orange County Register]]|accessdate=2008-09-24|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081007163257/http://www.ocregister.com/articles/deleon-trial-jurors-2166497-first-case|archivedate=2008-10-07}}</ref> In a consolidated case, Deleon was jointly tried for the murders of Thomas and Jackie Hawks as well as the murder of John Jarvi. Despite Deleon's earlier protestations of innocence, once his trial began, Deleon's attorney conceded that Deleon had indeed committed all three murders. The attorney said that he had taken the case to trial only to argue to a jury that Deleon should not be sentenced to death.<ref>{{cite news|date=2008-10-08 |url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/10/07/yacht.killings.trial.ap/index.html?iref=newssearch |title=Ex-actor guilty of yacht killings, defense says |work=[[CNN.com]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024113539/http://www.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/10/07/yacht.killings.trial.ap/index.html?iref=newssearch |archivedate=October 24, 2008 }}</ref> On October 20, Deleon was convicted of three counts of first-degree murder with special circumstances for financial gain and multiple victims and on November 6, 2008, the jury rendered a death verdict.<ref>{{cite news |first=My-Thuan |last=Tran |title=Death sentence in murder of yacht owners |url=http://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-deleon7-2008nov07,0,1127851.story |work=Los Angeles Times |publisher= |date=2008-11-06 |accessdate=2008-11-07 }}</ref> Sentencing was originally scheduled for January 16, 2009,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/11/06/yacht.killings.ap/index.html |title=Jury recommends death penalty in yacht killings |date=November 6, 2008 |publisher=[[CNN.com]] |accessdate=2008-11-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081110100734/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/11/06/yacht.killings.ap/index.html |archivedate=November 10, 2008 }}</ref> but was then rescheduled to March 20 on request by Deleon's attorney.<ref>{{cite web|first=Joseph|last=Serna|url=http://www.dailypilot.com/articles/2009/01/16/topstory/dpt-sentencing011709.txt|title=Sentencing delayed for area couple\u2019s killer|date=January 16, 2009|publisher=dailypilot.com|accessdate=2009-01-24}}</ref> On March 13, it was announced that sentencing would again be rescheduled, to April 10, so that the family of the victims could attend.<ref>{{cite web|first=Joseph|last=Serna|url=http://www.dailypilot.com/articles/2009/03/20/topstory/dpt-deleonsentencing032109.txt|title=Deleon to wait for his fate|date=March 13, 2009|publisher=dailypilot.com|accessdate=2009-03-27}}</ref> On April 10, 2009, Deleon was sentenced to death by Orange County Superior Court Judge Frank Fasel.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2009/04/skylar-deleon-gets-death-sentence-in-newport-yacht-murders.html|title=Skylar Deleon gets death sentence in Newport Beach yacht murders|date=April 10, 2009|publisher=[[latimes.com]]|accessdate=2009-04-11}}</ref> He is on [[death row]] at [[San Quentin State Prison]].\n\nOn February 19, 2009, John Fitzgerald Kennedy was found guilty on two counts of first degree murder after fewer than three hours of jury deliberation.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Welborn|first1=Larry|title=3rd man convicted in murders of couple on yacht|url=http://www.ocregister.com/news/deleon-111998-kennedy-hawks.html|website=The Orange County Register|publisher=Digital First Media|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref> He was sentenced to death on May 1, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Serna|first1=Joseph|title=Second killer given death|url=http://articles.dailypilot.com/2009-05-01/news/dpt-kennedy05022009_1_skylar-deleon-sentenced-penalty|website=Daily Pilot|publisher=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref> Like Deleon, Kennedy is on death row at [[San Quentin State Prison]].\n\nAlonso Machain, after testifying against Deleon, Henderson, and Kennedy, pleaded guilty to two counts each of voluntary manslaughter, kidnapping, and robbery. On June 15, 2009, he was sentenced to 20 years, 4 months. He likely will not be up for parole until 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/machain-113743-deleon-hawks.html?page=2|title=Final defendant in yacht-murder case pleads guilty|work=[[Orange County Register]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref> He is currently serving his sentence at [[Valley State Prison]] in [[Chowchilla, California]].<ref name=\"State of California Inmate Locator\"/>\n\nIn March 2009, after spending four years incarcerated, Myron Gardner pleaded guilty to \"accessory after the fact\" and the murder charges against him were dropped.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/man-sentenced-in-drowning-of-yacht-owners/|title=Man Sentenced In Drowning Of Yacht Owners|date=11 April 2009|work=[[CBS News]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jun/20/local/me-death-boat20|title=Murdered couple's yacht to be put up for sale|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.dailypilot.com/2009-03-26/news/dpt-gardner032709_1_ryan-hawks-myron-gardner-skylar-deleon|title=Man is freed in plea deal|work=[[Daily Pilot]]|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==In the media==\n* This case was investigated on TV by [[Aphrodite Jones]] in her [[Investigation Discovery]] documentary TV series ''True Crime with Aphrodite Jones'' (Season 1, episode 9), and would also be explored on the same network on two other programs: ''Wicked Attraction'' (episode \"Calm Before the Storm\") and ''Deadly Sins'' (episode \"I'd Kill For A Sex Change\").\n* This case is referred to in a segment of the \"Caffeine-Induced Aneurysm\" episode of ''[[Robot Chicken]]''.\n* This case was investigated on TV on [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] on the TV show ''[[Snapped: Killer Couples]]'', a spin-off of ''[[Snapped]]''.\n* The ''[[48 Hours (TV series)|48 Hours]]'' episode \"Dark Voyage\" covers this crime.\n* The ''[[Demons in the City of Angels]]'' episode ''Child Actor Killer'' covers the case.\n* This case is also covered in the podcast \"Killafornia Dreaming: True Crime Tales from the Golden State; Episode 14, The Tale of Lost at Sea\" - Google Play Podcasts\n* This case is briefly mentioned in the Podcast \"Raised by TV\" hosted by comedians [[Lauren Lapkus]] and [[Jon Gabrus]] in the episode \"Mt. Crushmore\".\n* This case is covered on the TV show [[Crime Watch Daily]] with Chris Hansen, Season 2, Episode 165, \"The Final Voyage\"\n* This case is mentioned in the podcast \"My Favorite Murder\" in the Episode 169, \"This Old Sandwich\"\n*This case was investigated on [[ABC 20/20]] episode \u201cOverboard\u201d\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{cite book|title=Dead Reckoning|author=[[Caitlin Rother]]|publisher=Kensington|year=2011|isbn=9780786022175}}\n* {{cite book|title=Vanished at Sea|author=Tina Dirmann|publisher=Macmillan|year=2008|isbn=9780312941970}}\n* {{cite news|date=2005-08-15 |title=Yacht murder case looks like true-crime sequel |author=Frank Mickadeit |url=http://www.ocregister.com/ocr/sections/local/local_columns/article_632770.php |work=[[Orange County Register|Orange County Register Communications]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090210113934/http://www.ocregister.com/ocr/sections/local/local_columns/article_632770.php |archivedate=February 10, 2009 }}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Capital punishment in California]]\n* [[List of solved missing persons cases]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|2117623|Skylar Deleon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hawks, Thomas and Jackie}}\n[[Category:2000s missing person cases]]\n[[Category:2004 in California]]\n[[Category:2004 murders in the United States]]\n[[Category:American murder victims]]\n[[Category:Deaths by person in the United States]]\n[[Category:History of Orange County, California]]\n[[Category:Missing person cases in California]]\n[[Category:Murder convictions without a body]]\n[[Category:Newport Beach, California]]\n[[Category:People murdered in California]]\n", "name_user": "Scottiebhoy670", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Murder_of_Thomas_and_Jackie_Hawks"}
{"title_page": "Jim Sturgess", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Jim Sturgess\n| image          =Jim Sturgess (8122044956).jpg\n| imagesize      =\n| alt            =\n| birthname      = James Anthony Sturgess\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1978|05|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Wandsworth]], [[London]], [[England]], UK<ref>https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QV49-9XJX</ref>\n| nationality    = English\n| alma_mater     = [[University of Salford]]\n| occupation     = {{hlist|Actor|singer-songwriter}}\n| years_active   = 1994\u2013present\n| spouse           = {{marriage|[[Dina Mousawi]]|2019}}\n| partner        =\n| module         =\n {{Infobox musical artist\n |embed           = yes\n |name            = Musical career\n |background      = solo_singer\n |instrument      = {{hlist|Vocals|guitar|piano|drums}}\n |label           =\n |years_active    = 1996\u2013present\n |associated_acts = Dilated Spies<br/>Saint Faith\n  }}\n}}\n'''James Anthony \"Jim\" Sturgess'''<ref name=birth>''Births, Marriages & Deaths Index of England & Wales, 1916\u20132005.''; at ancestry.com</ref> (born 16 May 1978)<!--- significant evidence that he was born in 1978, including articles and... his birth certificate. The University of Salford lists him as a 1999 graduate, see http://staff.salford.ac.uk/news/details/974 ---><ref>{{cite web|last=Symkus |first=Ed |url=http://www.cantonrep.com/entertainment/x27449597/Anne-Hathaway-Jim-Sturgess-trace-their-paths-to-One-Day |title=Anne Hathaway, Jim Sturgess trace their paths to 'One Day' \u2013 Entertainment \u2013 Canton, OH |publisher=CantonRep.com |date=15 August 2011 |accessdate=6 April 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925204813/http://www.cantonrep.com/entertainment/x27449597/Anne-Hathaway-Jim-Sturgess-trace-their-paths-to-One-Day |archivedate=25 September 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shortlist.com/entertainment/films/jim-sturgess-interview |title=Jim Sturgess Interview \u2013 Films \u2013 ShortList Magazine |publisher=Shortlist.com |date= |accessdate=6 April 2013}}</ref><ref name=wusvus>{{cite web |url=http://staff.salford.ac.uk/news/details/974 |title=News &#124; Staff Channel &#124; University of Salford \u2013 A Greater Manchester University |publisher=Staff.salford.ac.uk |date=9 April 2009 |accessdate=6 April 2013}}</ref> is an English actor and singer-songwriter.<ref>{{cite web |date=28 March 2008 |last=Scott |first=Mike |title=Actor Jim Sturgess' Career Is Poised for takeoff |url=http://blog.nola.com/mikescott/2008/03/actor_jim_sturgess_career_is_p.html |quote=I think Julie definitely was into the fact that I was a musician. |access-date=3 October 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120829171730/http://blog.nola.com/mikescott/2008/03/actor_jim_sturgess_career_is_p.html |archive-date=29 August 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> His first major role was as Jude in the [[musical film|musical]] [[romance film|romance]] drama film ''[[Across the Universe (film)|Across the Universe]]'' (2007).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/across_the_universe/ |title=Rotten Tomatoes Reviews of ''Across the Universe'' |website= [[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate= 7 June 2011}}</ref> In 2008, he played the male lead role of Ben Campbell in ''[[21 (2008 film)|21]]''. In 2009, he played Gavin Kossef in the crime drama ''[[Crossing Over (film)|Crossing Over]]'', appearing with [[Harrison Ford]], [[Ray Liotta]], and [[Ashley Judd]]. In 2010, Sturgess starred in the film ''[[The Way Back (2010 film)|The Way Back]]'', directed by [[Peter Weir]]. Sturgess co-starred in the epic science fiction film ''[[Cloud Atlas (film)|Cloud Atlas]]'', which began filming in September 2011 and was released in October 2012.\n\n==Personal life==\n{{Refimprovesection|date=February 2020}}\nSturgess was born in [[Wandsworth]], London, but grew up in [[Farnham]], [[Surrey]], where he attended [[Frensham Heights School]]. He spent most of his youth skateboarding in local car parks and started his first band when he was about 15 years old. The band played gigs in and around his local area. Sturgess's first acting experience came when a local theatre group came to his school looking for children to audition for a play. Sturgess went along to the audition and landed one of the parts in the play.\n\nSturgess moved to [[Manchester]] to attend the [[University of Salford]] in the hope that it would enable him to continue his music and take part in the Manchester music scene. In Manchester, he fell in with a group of aspiring actors and film makers, and his acting efforts began to become productive. He started to write and perform his own short films and plays. While performing a one-person show 'BUZZIN', based on his performance poetry, Jim was discovered by an acting agent. He graduated from the University of Salford in 1999 with an HND in Media and Performance.<ref name=\"wusvus\"/>\n\nIn July 2019, Sturgess married theatre producer [[Dina Mousawi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/jim-sturgess-brings-hoax-with-a-painful-legacy-to-life-in-new-jt-leroy-biopic-a4215026.html/ | title=Jim Sturgess brings hoax with a painful legacy to life in new JT LeRoy biopic |date=2015-03-12 |accessdate=2019-08-16}}</ref>\n\n==Acting career==\nIn 2007, he was cast in [[Julie Taymor]]'s musical ''[[Across the Universe (film)|Across the Universe]]'', portraying Jude Feeny, a young man who travels to the US amid the raging throes of the late 1960s and falls in love with a sheltered American teenager, Lucy, played by [[Evan Rachel Wood]].\n\nIn 2008, he appeared in the historical drama ''[[The Other Boleyn Girl (2008 film)|The Other Boleyn Girl]]'' in the supporting role of [[George Boleyn]] opposite [[Natalie Portman]], [[Scarlett Johansson]], and [[Eric Bana]]. He also played the male lead role of Ben Campbell in ''[[21 (2008 film)|21]]'', a film about five [[MIT Blackjack Team|MIT students]] who, by counting cards, take [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]] casinos for millions. Sturgess's co-stars in ''21'' include [[Kevin Spacey]] and [[Laurence Fishburne]].\n\nIn 2009, he played Gavin Kossef in ''[[Crossing Over (film)|Crossing Over]]'', appearing with [[Harrison Ford]], [[Ray Liotta]], and [[Ashley Judd]]. Set in Los Angeles, the story revolves around immigrants from different countries and backgrounds who share a common bond: they are all desperately trying to gain legal-immigrant status. Also in 2009, he starred in [[Kari Skogland]]'s critically acclaimed \u2018'[[Fifty Dead Men Walking]]'\u2019, loosely based on the true story related in a best-selling book by [[Martin McGartland]], of a young [[Northern Ireland|Northern Irishman]] who is recruited by the British police to infiltrate and spy on the [[Provisional Irish Republican Army|Irish Republican Army]], and who in the process ends up saving about 50 innocent lives.\n\n''[[Heartless (2009 film)|Heartless]]'', a film directed by [[Philip Ridley]], premiered on 31 August 2009<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frightfest.co.uk/09films/film25.html |title=film25 |publisher=[[London FrightFest Film Festival]] |date=31 August 2009 |accessdate=7 June 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718101046/http://www.frightfest.co.uk/09films/film25.html |archivedate=18 July 2011 }}</ref> at the [[London FrightFest Film Festival]], a popular horror film festival. Sturgess appears as Jamie Morgan, a young man whose life has always been blighted by the large, heart-shaped port wine birthmark on his face and sells his soul to the devil. Jim Sturgess won the Best Actor Award at the 2010 [[Fantasporto]] Film Festival for his role. The film also won the Best Film Award and the Best Director Award for [[Philip Ridley]].\n\nIn 2010, Sturgess starred in the film ''[[The Way Back (2010 film)|The Way Back]]'', directed by [[Peter Weir]] and based on a true story. The character Sturgess plays is based on [[S\u0142awomir Rawicz]], a young Polish officer who escaped from a Russian [[gulag]] during World War II. Also in 2010, he did voice-over work for director [[Zack Snyder]]'s 3-D animated feature film ''[[Legend of the Guardians: The Owls of Ga'Hoole]]'', based on the children's book series ''[[Guardians of Ga'Hoole]]'' by [[Kathryn Lasky]], in which he voiced Soren, the main protagonist of the film. He was originally set to voice Soren's brother Kludd, one of the main antagonists, but the part went to [[Ryan Kwanten]].\n\nIn May 2010, Sturgess signed on to appear in ''[[One Day (2011 film)|One Day]]'' (based on the [[One Day (novel)|novel of the same title]] by [[David Nicholls (writer)|David Nicholls]]) with [[Anne Hathaway]]. The novel, about two students who meet on 15 July 1988, follows them on every 15 July for the next 20 years. Directed by [[Lone Scherfig]],<ref>{{cite web| author = Goodridge, Mike |url=http://www.screendaily.com/news/production/hathaway-sturgess-sign-to-scherfigs-one-day-for-focus/5013651.article |title=Hathaway, Sturgess Sign to Scherfig's One Day for Focus | work = [[Screen International]] |date= 12 May 2010 |accessdate= 7 June 2011}}</ref> filming was completed on 17 September 2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tribute.ca/interviews/jim+sturgess/star/43101 |title=Jim Sturgess (Legend of the Guardians: The Owls of Ga'Hoole) Interview  | work = [[Tribute (magazine)|Tribute]] |date= |accessdate= 7 June 2011}}</ref> and had its theatrical release in August 2011.\n\nAlso during 2010, he filmed ''[[Upside Down (2012 film)|Upside Down]]''. Filming was completed in May 2010 in [[Montreal]], and as of early 2013 a limited international release was planned.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1374992/|title=Upside Down (2012)|publisher=IMDb.com|accessdate=6 April 2013}}</ref> Described as a \"sci-fi romance\", the film is the second full-length feature from writer and director [[Juan Solanas]]. It was originally slated for release in 2011,<ref>{{cite web| url= http://jimsturgessonline.com/?p=4159 |title='Upside Down' Teaser Poster |publisher=Jimsturgessonline.com |date= 26 May 2010 |accessdate= 7 June 2011}}</ref> but delays pushed back the release date.\n\nA third film project in 2010 was ''Promised Land'', to be directed by [[Michael Winterbottom]] and, according to ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', would \"recount the lead up to the 1948 partition of [[Palestine (region)|Palestine]] and the subsequent creation of the state of Israel\". Sturgess was to star as a British officer hunting down the extremist Jewish factions. The film was later put on hiatus because funding could not be secured.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://movies.uk.msn.com/news/winterbottom-wants-promised-land-1|title= Winterbottom wants Promised Land|publisher= msn.com|date= 12 July 2012|access-date= 9 August 2012|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120719204423/http://movies.uk.msn.com/news/winterbottom-wants-promised-land-1|archive-date= 19 July 2012|url-status= dead}}</ref>\n\nIn March and April 2011, filming took place for ''[[Ashes (2012 film)|Ashes]]'',<ref>{{cite web|last=Cooper |first=Sarah |url=http://www.screendaily.com/reports/features/untitled-mat-whitecross-project/5027277.article |title=Untitled Mat Whitecross Project &#124; Features &#124; Screen |publisher=Screendaily.com |date=12 May 2011 |accessdate=6 April 2013}}</ref> a film directed by Mat Whitecross. The picture has been described as a contemporary film noir thriller starring [[Ray Winstone]] and [[Lesley Manville]] along with Sturgess. Filmed in the [[Isle of Man]], the production was partially funded by the band [[Coldplay]], university friends of the director.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/archives/ray_winstone_jim_sturgess_lesley_manville_team_for_noir_ashes_film/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716043215/http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/archives/ray_winstone_jim_sturgess_lesley_manville_team_for_noir_ashes_film/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=16 July 2011 |title=Ray Winstone, Jim Sturgess & Lesley Manville Team For Noir 'Ashes'; Film Co-Financed By Coldplay |publisher=The Playlist (blog of [[indieWire]]) |accessdate=7 June 2011 }}</ref> Sturgess co-starred in ''[[Cloud Atlas (film)|Cloud Atlas]]'', which began filming in September 2011 and was released in October 2012.\n\nSturgess worked on two films during 2012. [[Giuseppe Tornatore|Giuseppe Tornatore's]] ''[[The Best Offer]]'' (original title 'La Migliore Offerta') was filmed during the spring in [[Prague]], [[Vienna]], and several cities in Italy. Co-starring [[Geoffrey Rush]] and [[Sylvia Hoeks]], the film went on to win the [[David di Donatello for Best Film|David di Donatello Award]] for Best Film. In the autumn, Sturgess went to [[Los Angeles]] to film ''[[Electric Slide (film)|Electric Slide]]'', directed by Tristan Patterson and co-starring [[Isabel Lucas]] and [[Chloe Sevigny]]. An official selection of the [[Tribeca Film Festival]], it premiered there in 2014 as part of the Viewpoint selections.<ref>{{cite web |title=Here Are the 22 Films in the Viewpoints Section |url=http://www.tribecafilmfestival.org/stories/tribeca-film-festival-viewpoints-2014 |publisher=[[Tribeca Film Festival]] |date=4 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140314134135/http://www.tribecafilmfestival.org/stories/tribeca-film-festival-viewpoints-2014 |archivedate=14 March 2014 |url-status=dead |accessdate=6 November 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nIn the last half of 2013, Sturgess worked in three films. The first was ''[[Stonehearst Asylum]]'', co-starring [[Kate Beckinsale]] and directed by [[Brad Anderson (director)|Brad Anderson]], in the summer. Loosely based on the short story \"[[The System of Doctor Tarr and Professor Fether]]\" by [[Edgar Allan Poe]], Sturgess stars as a medical school graduate who visits an asylum for the insane. The film was released in October 2014. ''[[London Fields (2014 film)|London Fields]]'', based on the novel by [[Martin Amis]], was next, filmed in [[London]] and co-starring [[Amber Heard]] and [[Billy Bob Thornton]]. The picture is the first feature film directed by [[Mathew Cullen]]. After that, ''[[Kidnapping Freddy Heineken]]'' was filmed in Belgium and [[New Orleans]]. Directed by [[Daniel Alfredson]] and co-starring [[Sam Worthington]] and [[Anthony Hopkins]], filming finished before the end of the year. It was released in 2015. Sturgess portrayed Dutch criminal [[Cor van Hout]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/567104/Freddy-Heineken-abduction-new-film-with-Anthony-Hopkins|title=Kidnapping of the Freddy Heineken- the beer tycoon|last=Midgley|first=Dominic|publisher=Express|date=30 March 2015|accessdate=9 October 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009143656/http://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/567104/Freddy-Heineken-abduction-new-film-with-Anthony-Hopkins|archivedate=9 October 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Music career==\n{{Refimprove section|date=February 2020}}\n{{Listen\n |filename = Jim_Sturgess_Panic_&_Magic.ogg\n |title = \"Panic & Magic\"\n |description = Sturgess has written music related to both ''[[Crossing Over (film)|Crossing Over]]'' and ''[[Heartless (2009 film)|Heartless]]''}}\nSturgess has been writing and performing his own music since the age of 15. He has appeared in the London music scene for many years in bands such as Saint Faith and Dilated Spies. He has also written music for some of his films, including two tracks that he wrote and performed for ''[[Crossing Over (film)|Crossing Over]]'', and he collaborated with director [[Philip Ridley]] on three tracks that appeared in the film ''[[Heartless (2009 film)|Heartless]]''. [[Mickey O'Brien]]; his ex girlfriend was the composer of the trailer track \"Panic And Magic\"<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jBFFkbrkAkc</ref> and Jim provided the vocals.\n\nIn 2016, he released five exclusive demos with his band Tragic Toys, to raise funds for a friend with an aggressive form of multiple sclerosis. The music for these demos were written by ex-girlfriend and La Roux member [[Mickey O'Brien]] and Jim provided the vocals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/08/17/one-day-interview_n_928902.html|title=One Day Interview: Jim Sturgess Might Not Be Here Tomorrow|last=Emami|first=Gazelle|website=Huffington Post|date=17 August 2011|accessdate=26 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:50px;\"| Year\n! style=\"width:250px;\"| Title\n! style=\"width:150px;\"| Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''{{sortname|The|Browning Version|dab=1994 film}}''\n| Bryant\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Mouth to Mouth (2005 British film)|Mouth to Mouth]]''\n| Red\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Across the Universe (film)|Across the Universe]]''\n| Jude Feeny\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''{{sortname|The|Other Boleyn Girl|dab=2008 film}}''\n| [[George Boleyn]]\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[21 (2008 film)|21]]''\n| Ben Campbell\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Fifty Dead Men Walking]]''\n| [[Martin McGartland]]\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Crossing Over (film)|Crossing Over]]''\n| Gavin Kossef\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Heartless (2009 film)|Heartless]]''\n| Jamie Morgan\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''{{sortname|The|Way Back|dab=2010 film}}''\n| Janusz Wieszczek\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Legend of the Guardians: The Owls of Ga'Hoole]]''\n| Soren\n| Voice role\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[One Day (2011 film)|One Day]]''\n| Dexter Mayhew\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Ashes (2012 film)|Ashes]]''\n| James\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Cloud Atlas (film)|Cloud Atlas]]''\n| Adam Ewing/Poor Hotel Guest/Megan's Dad/Highlander/Hae-Joo Chang\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[The Best Offer]]''\n| Robert\n|''Italiano: [[La migliore offerta]] / UK: [[The Best Offer|Deception]]''\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Upside Down (2012 film)|Upside Down]]''\n| Adam\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Electric Slide (film)|Electric Slide]]''\n